{"in": {"title": "Questing Lores", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">a blank slate is the best slate</span>", "lines": ["ED: In AS YOU LIKE IT - to a Buddhist beat", "ED: The great bard said that all the world's a stage,", "ED: And all the men and women merely players -", "ED: No matter what their stature, rank or age:", "ED: The brand new babe of countless rosy wrinkles", "ED: With cry that's pacified at tender breast", "ED: And crone who's like a prune that's past its prime", "ED: Oozing regrets crying for her rest -", "ED: The maudlin maiden pining for her lover", "ED: Who full of ambition would rather seek", "ED: The bubble reputation than her kiss", "ED: That passed instead to melancholy's cheek -", "ED: The bonded bitch, her body but a bag", "ED: Of bones, of blood, of bastard bearing skin;", "ED: Her master, with a hungry whip, no friend", "ED: To kindness, mercy, all their kith and kin -", "ED: The tyrant king but ever faithful husband", "ED: To cruel caprice, lacking sense and reason;", "ED: The guiltless traitor, victim of the envies", "ED: Framed by friends to deadly charge of treason.", "ED: But him, I'm not, and them I'd never be.", "ED: With all anxieties ashed in tranquil peace", "ED: I see the play unfold although I'm there -", "ED: A puppet with my name and pledge to please.", "ED: My mind's emptied of fear and every care", "ED: It's spared those searing looks from jealous eyes;", "ED: By being not an actor but spectator", "ED: It dodges caustic pens of savage slice.", "ED: I have no feet and yet I skip and dance", "ED: I have no mouth, but still I speak and sing.", "ED: I loudly hear and clearly see and am", "ED: Sans ears, sans eyes, sans head, sans everything."], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Joanna", "ED": "Amy"}}, "out": {"cache_id": "d1e93e349f75b7a4ad46cab78a36ef5e", "audio_objects": [["b1aa467d6a3453f65bc2753c05fb00a1-in-as-you-like-it---to-a----", 0], ["f166fc273790d91f690e794df188a101-the-great-bard-said-that----", 0], ["672e86df2e2f4238